    <mj-section padding-top="30px">
      <mj-column width="100%">
        <mj-text>
          <p style="font-weight: bold">Welcome!</p>
          <p>There was some discussion in the <a href="https://t.me/devopsish">DevOps&rsquo;ish Telegram</a> about what the topic of this intro should be this week. One suggestion was excellent; I&rsquo;m probably going to run with it next week. But, I understand that there are some of you looking for something to learn while we&rsquo;re in this odd time. I wrote this week&rsquo;s newsletter with that in mind. <a href="https://youtu.be/K5qI9bTG9Ik">If you don&rsquo;t know <code>git</code>, <strong>now</strong> is the time to learn</a> for sure. Please don&rsquo;t hesitate to reach out if you have any feedback. Thank you for subscribing and reading.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section>
      <mj-column width="75%">
        <mj-divider border-width="2px" border-color="#666"></mj-divider>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section>
      <mj-column width="100%">
        <mj-text padding-bottom="0px">
          <h2 style="font-weight: bold">People</h2>
          <p><a href="https://www.cncf.io/blog/2020/04/03/were-all-in-this-together-a-wellness-guide-from-the-cncf-well-being-working-group/">We&rsquo;re all in this Together: A Wellness Guide from the CNCF Well-Being Working Group</a><br />
            If you&rsquo;re struggling, I&rsquo;m right there with you. Don&rsquo;t be afraid to reach out for help.</p>

          <p><a href="https://devops.com/ibm-awards-its-second-50000-open-source-community-grant-to-internship-and-mentorship-program-outreachy/">IBM awards its second $50,000 Open Source Community Grant to internship and mentorship program Outreachy</a><br />
            &ldquo;Our open source community nominated a number of nonprofits doing incredible work and, while voting was close with plenty of deserving organizations in the mix, we awarded Outreachy the most votes for their commitment to providing paid internships to underserved and underrepresented minorities.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.jeffgeerling.com/blog/2020/my-devops-books-are-free-april-thanks-device42">Jeff Geerling&rsquo;s DevOps books are free in April, thanks to Device42</a><br />
            Huge thanks for these books. Ansible for DevOps changed my career. Ansible for Kubernetes builds on that. Thank you!</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/video-games/2020/04/03/best-video-games-modern-nintendo-playstation-xbox-pc/?utm_source=reddit.com">The best games to play while waiting out the coronavirus</a><br />
            I will freely admit, I&rsquo;m looking for distractions from the news and numbers.</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.cnn.com/2020/04/02/tech/wework-softbank-bailout/index.html">WeWork founder Adam Neumann loses out as SoftBank scraps share buyout</a><br />
            <em>points and laughs</em></p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section>
      <mj-column width="75%">
        <mj-divider border-width="2px" border-color="#666"></mj-divider>
