    <mj-section>
      <mj-column width="100%">
        <mj-text padding-bottom="0px">
          <h2 style="font-weight: bold">Process</h2>
          <p><a href="https://blog.sensu.io/migrating-to-kubernetes">Migrating to Kubernetes</a><br />
            &ldquo;How to migrate depends, to an extent, on what you want to migrate from. The primary consideration is whether your existing infrastructure runs workloads in containers. If so, you&rsquo;re already off to a quick start because you won&rsquo;t have the containerization step to complete. Otherwise, you have a clear place to start.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.zdnet.com/article/a-hacker-has-wiped-defaced-more-than-15000-elasticsearch-servers/">A hacker has wiped, defaced more than 15,000 Elasticsearch servers</a><br />
            &ldquo;Hacker tries to pin the blame on Night Lion Security, a US cyber-security firm.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.ansible.com/blog/ops-by-pull-request-an-ansible-gitops-story">Ops by Pull Request: An Ansible GitOps Story</a><br />
            &ldquo;There are many tools you can use in your GitOps pipelines; however, Ansible provides some unique advantages that make it ideal for these workflows and extending their use beyond Kubernetes and cloud-native systems.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://candor.co/hiring-freezes/">Who&rsquo;s freezing hiring from coronavirus</a><br />
            A continuously updated AirTable of companies and whether or not they&rsquo;re hiring.</p>

          <p><a href="https://hbr.org/2020/04/3-tips-to-avoid-wfh-burnout">3 Tips to Avoid WFH Burnout</a><br />
            &ldquo;Maintain physical and social boundaries. Maintain temporal boundaries as much as possible. Focus on your most important work.&rdquo;</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section>
